channel.title: [Request] Deobfuscated 204
channel.description:
I successfully recovered my old high-level pure that I thought was long gone (due to many unsuccessful recovery attempts over the years) and found that I've still got RSC access :D.
I have searched and followed many links to no avail. Please upload a deobfuscated version of the current mudclient.
Also, if you have any old sources laying around, please share. I've scoured these forums and so far the only source I was able to find was TLM. I'd love to get ahold of InfinitBoT, TBoT or SBoT6.0. If you're uncomfortable posting uploads, feel free to pm them to me.
And don't worry, this is all for private use, learning, and nostalgia. None of your/others work is going to be whored around the RSC community or used to turn a profit.

[/quote]It’s not hard…he included a shell script if I’m not mistaken?[/quote]

Yes he did, but I’m on windows vista and I haven’t messed with this stuff for around 3-4 years. I’m really rusty with Java and I’d much rather just have someone post a deob or walk me through creating my own using saevs code. I know it sounds a bit lazy but if I thought it was within my current abilities to go about it alone I would have already done so. As I said, I extensively searched the forums only to find broken/dead links. This thread was a last resort.

I appreciate all of the replies but unfortunately none of them have really had anything to do with my request (with the exception of bundy’s first post, kinda)
